<b>Original Post</b><p>
<table bgcolor="#000000" width="100%" cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 border=0>
<tr><td>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 border=0>
<tr>
<td bgcolor="#CECECE" class="btext" width="100%"><b>Opera Released</b> - <span class=bsmall>posted by  <a class='nNewsMailLink' href='mailto:deathwatch@barrysworld.com'>Deathwatch</a> on Mon 09 July 2001 17:43:42 | <a href="comments.php?section=1&index=237" class=blink>Comments (0)</a></span></td>
<td bgcolor="#CECECE" width=17><img src="images/item_icon.gif" width="17" height="17" alt="" border="0"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2 class=news>
<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_general.gif' alt='General News' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top>After a long long time, <a href="http://opera.redeemedsoft.com/" class=colourise>The Opera</a> (Halflife mod) has it's first release.<br><br>This mod offers gameplay which is supposed to match the Honk Kong action movies (hmmz, doesn't Action Quake 2 do that as well) and some interesting changes, like awarding stylish kills:<br><br><span class=quote>"For example: riddling a body with bullets from an Uzi while standing still may net you a couple of hundred bucks. Killing someone in one blow with a knife slash to the head while diving will earn you a few thousand."</span><br><br>You also have several weapons at your disposal, such as a lot of pistols and some submachineguns and a few more. Also, there is no health or ammo indication, with exception when you got the right discipline.<br><br>Disciplines are attributes of your character that makes you different from the rest. The attributes offer faster speed or that you can take more damage, or that you are silent, etc.<br><br>All in all, this mod looks very promising, especially if you are looking for some fast paced action.<br><br>Download it from <a href="ftp://ftp.barrysworld.com/pub/games/halflife/mods/opera/opera_r1.exe" class=bwlink>here</a> from the <a href="http://www.barrysworld.com" class=bwlink>BarrysWorld</a> FTP. (about 87 mb)</td></tr></table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
